We'll use common Python libraries. You'll need to install them:
pip install opencv-python scikit-image pytesseract pdfplumber spacy pandas numpy scikit-learn tensorflow (or pytorch)

1. requirements.txt

# Core Libraries
pandas
numpy
scikit-learn
matplotlib
seaborn
# Document Processing
pdfplumber
Pillow # PIL fork, often installed with other libs
pytesseract
# Computer Vision
opencv-python
scikit-image
# NLP (if using rule-based parsing or custom models)
spacy
# Deep Learning (for advanced CV/NLP or multimodal)
tensorflow # or pytorch
transformers # for pre-trained models
# FastAPI (for API, if you want a web service)
fastapi
uvicorn